name: float_f32_positive_zero
description: |
  IEEE 754 binary32 positive zero has all bits clear. It compares equal to
  negative zero, but its sign affects division, reciprocals, copysign, and some
  branch-cut functions. It is also paired with the smallest subnormal to expose
  implementations that flush tiny non-zero values to zero.
format: hex
decode-as: f32
pair:
  - with: negative-zero.input
    hint: equal
  - with: smallest-positive-subnormal.input
    hint: not-equal
tags:
  - "float"
  - "floating-point"
  - "ieee-754"
  - "f32"
  - "signed-zero"
---
00 00 00 00   # 0x00000000: +0
